    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Components of some belts, especially those that formed a part of early medieval dress: a counter plate was placed opposite the buckle. These were found on belts that would have included a buckle, and sometimes a rectangular back plate placed in the middle of the belt at the back for decoration.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
